## D1 Enforcement Layering
Definitional Extension, 5.5.

Rationale: P5 (probabilistic interpretation) + L1тАУL6 (hierarchy of boundary conditions)

By P5, normative guidelines are only probabilistically complied with.
Therefore, absolute constraints such as L1 (safety) should be
implemented via structural enforcement (not subject to probabilistic interpretation).

Connection with terminology reference:
- Structural enforcement тЖТ Invariant (┬з9.3): Property that always holds during execution
- Procedural enforcement тЖТ Pre/post-conditions (┬з9.3): Verified before and after operations
- Normative guideline тЖТ Satisfiable (┬з2.2) but not valid/tautological (┬з2.2) by P5

